From a0e578b574af4108d502fd8737a6c5678ba7e4f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: panasee <dongkai.pan@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 18:30:02 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Expose direct text payloads for remember HTTP ingestion

OpenClaw-style HTTP callers need to remember plain text without
uploading files. The router now accepts a single `text` field or
repeated `texts` form fields while preserving the existing uploaded
file path and dataset-selection behavior.

Constraint: Must preserve existing multipart file uploads and dataset selection semantics
Rejected: Add a new JSON-only endpoint | would duplicate the existing remember API surface
Confidence: high
Scope-risk: narrow
Directive: Keep text-vs-file precedence stable unless clients are migrated in lockstep
Tested: ruff check touched files; targeted unit test suite (49 passed)
Not-tested: End-to-end multipart requests against a live FastAPI server
---
